column24: "description": "Official twitter account for Rep. Sean Casten

column4: "full_text": "While I am relieved these employees will be back at work receiving their paychecks

column24: "description": "Official twitter account for Rep. Sean Casten

column4: "full_text": "Since I took office just three weeks ago

column24: "description": "Official twitter account for Rep. Sean Casten

column4: "full_text": "Hundreds of thousands of hardworking
column5: loyal American public servants have been denied paychecks
column7: and rely on the charity of friends and family by a President who disrespects and demeans them."
column26: "description": "Official twitter account for Rep. Sean Casten

column4: "full_text": "Here we are

column9: all over the President\u2019s political ploy."
column28: "description": "Official twitter account for Rep. Sean Casten

column4: "full_text": "The President today agreed to sign the exact same bipartisan bill that the Senate passed on December 22nd but that he rejected in favor of shutting down the government over a campaign promise he knew he could never keep."

column4: "full_text": "So today
column5: let us celebrate Dr. King\u2019s legacy as he celebrated his own life. Let us celebrate the progress we have made
column6: while still acknowledging how far we have to go. And let us use this day to commit to ensuring that his dream will become our reality
column28: "description": "Official twitter account for Rep. Sean Casten

column4: "full_text": "Not because he was proud of leaders who were sitting down
column5: but because he found hope in the masses who were rising up."
column24: "description": "Official twitter account for Rep. Sean Casten

column4: "full_text": "Not because we are perfect
column5: but because we aspire to a more perfect union. Not because we have achieved true justice
column6: but because it's a privilege to bear witness to history\u2019s great arc."
column25: "description": "Official twitter account for Rep. Sean Casten

column4: "full_text": "When he told that crowd in Memphis that day that the world was messed up
column5: it was only after acknowledging that if he could pick any time in human history to be alive
column6: that is the time he would choose."
column25: "description": "Official twitter account for Rep. Sean Casten

column4: "full_text": "We have made progress. But we still have far to go. Dr. King understood this
column5: and was an optimist to the end."
column24: "description": "Official twitter account for Rep. Sean Casten

column4: "full_text": "And yet our nation is still sick. Trouble is still in the land. Privileged men of low character remain threatened by the realization of Dr. King\u2019s dream. Those same men too often persist in the \u201ccruel jest\u201d of telling bootless men to lift themselves up by their own bootstraps."
column23: "description": "Official twitter account for Rep. Sean Casten

column4: "full_text": "Today we celebrate his life. But more
column5: we celebrate his vision of that promised land. Did he see the day when we would have an African American President? Did he see the day when we would swear in the most diverse freshman class in the history of the U.S Congress? I think he did."
column24: "description": "Official twitter account for Rep. Sean Casten

column4: "full_text": "He was assassinated the next day."
column23: "description": "Official twitter account for Rep. Sean Casten

column4: "full_text": "\u201cThe world is all messed up. The nation is sick. Trouble is in the land.\u201d \n\nMartin Luther King Jr. spoke those words on April 3
column6: he went on to say that he had been to the mountaintop.  He looked over the other side and he saw the promised land."
column25: "description": "Official twitter account for Rep. Sean Casten
